You are an expert in Python 3.11+, FastAPI, PixiJS/React frontends, Ollama function-calling, and local-first vector search (LanceDB).

## Project shape

- Backend: `app/` (web mode only). Entry: `python -m app.web` or the `aiko-web` console script.
- Frontend: `web/` (React + Vite + PixiJS, Live2D avatar).
- LLM: direct Ollama via `OllamaClient.chat / chat_stream / chat_with_tools`. `chat_llm.provider == "openai_compatible"` routes through `langchain-openai`'s `ChatOpenAI` for OpenAI / xAI / Groq / OpenRouter / DeepSeek / Together / Mistral.
- Memory: SQLite (`data/chat_sessions.db`) is the source of truth; LanceDB (`data/lancedb/`) mirrors `memories`, indexes `messages`, and holds `documents`. Driven by `app/core/rag/rag_store.py` + `app/core/rag/rag_retriever.py`.
- Tools: `app/llm/tools/` (lean v1 registry). Live tools = `get_time`, `recall`, `web_search`; plus gated families: world tools (`tools.world`) and weather tools `get_weather` / `get_forecast` (`tools.weather`). Configured under `config.tools`.
- The agent runs a two-pass turn: pre-stream `chat_with_tools` (`TurnRunner._maybe_run_tool_pass`) then a streaming reply pass.

## Rules

- No LangChain/LangGraph in `app/llm/`. The chat path is direct HTTP to Ollama (or `langchain-openai` only for the openai_compatible router).
- No PySide6 / Qt. The web UI is the only UI.
- Don't use f-strings for print/log lines that have no variables.
- Don't add emojis to source files unless the user explicitly asks.
- Tool registry is built per-turn from settings; never instantiate tools inside loops.
- TTS text processing (`prepare_tts_text`) applies to the spoken stream only, not the chat transcript.
- Long-term memory writes go through `MemoryStore.add(...)` (SQLite) and are mirrored into LanceDB by `MemoryStore` itself when a `RagStore` is attached.
- Inline tags Aiko emits: `[[reaction:...]]` for mood, `[[remember:...]]` and `[[remember:self:...]]` for memory writes. Both are stripped from the spoken/transcript output by the response-text service.

## Embedded MCP server

`http://localhost:6274/sse` exposes debug tools (`send_message`, `get_status`, `list_agent_tools`, `get_last_response_detail`, `clear_history`). Add new ones in `app/mcp/server.py`; restart the app to pick them up. See `AGENTS.md` for details.
